# MSB Ops — Directus UI Design (MVP)

## Overview

This document defines how the browser-based Directus UI will function for:

- Container Testing
- Display Testing
- Work Orders
- Stage browsing

The UI is task-focused and minimizes clutter.

---

# 1. Main Screens

## 1.1 Container Testing Dashboard

Collection: ops.v_container_testing_summary  
Display Name: "Container Testing"

Purpose:
Quickly see status of all containers.

Features:
- Filter by status (NOT_STARTED / IN_PROGRESS / DONE)
- Search by container_id, location_code, endpoint_name
- Columns:
  - container_id
  - endpoint
  - container_type
  - display_total
  - display_checked
  - display_remaining
  - last_checked_at

Clicking a row opens Container Focus screen.

---

## 1.2 Container Focus Screen

Collection:
- Header: filtered ops.v_container_testing_summary
- Child Grid: ops.v_container_testing_displays

Purpose:
Work on one container only.

Behavior:
- No other containers visible.
- Multiple users can mark displays complete simultaneously.
- Grid editable fields:
  - test_result
  - amps_measured
  - notes
  - checked_at

Display-only fields:
  - display_name
  - stage_name
  - string_type
  - color

Preset filters:
- Needs Repair (test_result = REPAIR)
- Repaired (test_result = REPAIRED)

---

## 1.3 Stage Browse

Collection: ops.v_stage_container_contents  
Display Name: "Stage Browse"

Purpose:
Select containers by stage and skill level.

Behavior:
- Group by stage
- See displays on each container
- View container_status

---

## 1.4 Work Orders

Collection: ops.v_work_order_open  
Display Name: "Work Orders"

Default sort:
- urgency DESC
- stage_name
- created_at

Clicking a row opens base table record (ops.work_order).

---

# 2. Work Order Detail Screen

Editable fields:
- urgency
- work_area_id
- notes
- date_completed
- completion_notes

On completion:
- Directus Flow updates related display_test_session
  - test_result = REPAIRED
  - checked_at set if null
  - checked_by derived from ref.person

---

# 3. Multi-User Behavior

- Multiple users can edit different display rows.
- Last save wins if conflict.
- No container locking in MVP.

---

# 4. Permissions Model (MVP)

Roles:

Viewer
- Read-only access to views.

Tester
- Edit ops.display_test_session.

Repair Lead
- Edit ops.work_order.

Admin
- Full access.

